1.definition: [Α] of Hebrew origin; the first letter of the alphabet; figuratively, only (from its use as a numeral) the first:  Often used (usually ἄν, before a vowel) also in composition (as a contraction from {{G427}}) in the sense of privation; so, in many words, beginning with this letter; occasionally in the sense of union (as a contraction of {{G260}}).

2.definition: [Ἀαρών] of Hebrew origin ({{H175}}); Aaron, the brother of Moses

3.definition: [Ἀβαδδών] of Hebrew origin ({{H11}}); a destroying angel

4.definition: [ἀβαρής] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G922}}; weightless, i.e. (figuratively) not burdensome

5.definition: [Ἀββᾶ] of Chaldee origin ({{H2}}); father as a vocative

6.definition: [Ἄβελ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1893}}); Abel, the son of Adam

7.definition: [Ἀβιά] of Hebrew origin ({{H29}}); Abijah, the name of two Israelites

8.definition: [Ἀβιαθάρ] of Hebrew origin ({{H54}}); Abiathar, an Israelite

9.definition: [Ἀβιληνή] of foreign origin (compare {{H58}}); Abilene, a region of Syria

10.definition: [Ἀβιούδ] of Hebrew origin ({{H31}}); Abihud, an Israelite

11.definition: [Ἀβραάμ] of Hebrew origin ({{H85}}); Abraham, the Hebrew patriarch (In Acts 7:16 the text should probably read Jacob.)

12.definition: [ἄβυσσος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a variation of {{G1037}}; depthless, i.e. (specially) (infernal) "abyss"

13.definition: [Ἄγαβος] of Hebrew origin (compare {{H2285}}); Agabus, an Israelite

15.definition: [ἀγαθοποιέω] from {{G17}}; to be a well-doer (as a favor or a duty)

17.definition: [ἀγαθοποιός] from {{G18}} and {{G4160}}; a well-doer, i.e. virtuous

18.definition: [ἀγαθός] a primary word; "good" (in any sense, often as noun) Compare {{G2570}}.

19.definition: [ἀγαθωσύνη] from {{G18}}; goodness, i.e. virtue or beneficence

21.definition: [ἀγαλλιάω] from agan (much) and {{G242}}; properly, to jump for joy, i.e. exult

22.definition: [ἄγαμος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G1062}}; unmarried

23.definition: [ἀγανακτέω] from ἄγαν (much) and ἄχθος (grief; akin to the base of {{G43}}); to be greatly afflicted, i.e. (figuratively) indignant

25.definition: [ἀγαπάω] perhaps from ἄγαν (much) (or compare {{H5689}}); to love (in a social or moral sense) Compare {{G5368}}.

26.definition: [ἀγάπη] from {{G25}}; love, i.e. affection or benevolence; specially (plural) a love-feast

28.definition: [Ἄγαρ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1904}}); Hagar, the concubine of Abraham

29.definition: [ἀγγαρεύω] of foreign origin (compare {{H104}}); properly, to be a courier, i.e. (by implication) to press into public service

30.definition: [ἀγγεῖον] from ἄγγος (a pail, perhaps as bent; compare the base of {{G43}}); a receptacle

31.definition: [ἀγγελία] from {{G32}}; an announcement, i.e. (by implication) precept

32.definition: [ἄγγελος] from ἀγγέλλω (probably derived from {{G71}}; compare {{G34}}) (to bring tidings); a messenger; especially an "angel"; by implication, a pastor

33.definition: [ἄγε] imperative of {{G71}}; properly, lead, i.e. come on

35.definition: [ἀγενεαλόγητος] from {{G1}} (as negative particle) and {{G1075}}; unregistered as to birth

36.definition: [ἀγενής] from {{G1}} (as negative particle) and {{G1085}}; properly, without kin, i.e. (of unknown descent, and by implication) ignoble

37.definition: [ἁγιάζω] from {{G40}}; to make holy, i.e. (ceremonially) purify or consecrate; (mentally) to venerate

38.definition: [ἁγιασμός] from {{G37}}; properly, purification, i.e. (the state) purity; concretely (by Hebraism) a purifier

39.definition: [ἅγιον] neuter of {{G40}}; a sacred thing (i.e. spot)

40.definition: [ἅγιος] from ἅγος (an awful thing) (compare {{G53}}, {{G2282}}); sacred (physically, pure, morally blameless or religious, ceremonially, consecrated)

43.definition: [ἀγκάλη] from ἄγκος (a bend, "ache"); an arm (as curved)

44.definition: [ἄγκιστρον] from the same as {{G43}}; a hook (as bent)

45.definition: [ἄγκυρα] from the same as {{G43}}; an "anchor" (as crooked)

46.definition: [ἄγναφος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and the same as {{G1102}}; properly, unfulled, i.e. (by implication) new (cloth)

48.definition: [ἁγνίζω] from {{G53}}; to make clean, i.e. (figuratively) sanctify (ceremonially or morally)

49.definition: [ἁγνισμός] from {{G48}}; a cleansing (the act), i.e. (ceremonially) lustration

50.definition: [ἀγνοέω] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G3539}}; not to know (through lack of information or intelligence); by implication, to ignore (through disinclination)

51.definition: [ἀγνόημα] from {{G50}}; a thing ignored, i.e. shortcoming

53.definition: [ἁγνός] from the same as {{G40}}; properly, clean, i.e. (figuratively) innocent, modest, perfect

56.definition: [ἀγνωσία] from {{G1}} (as negative particle) and {{G1108}}; ignorance (properly, the state)

58.definition: [ἀγορά] from ἀγείρω (to gather; probably akin to {{G1453}}); properly, the town-square (as a place of public resort); by implication, a market or thoroughfare

59.definition: [ἀγοράζω] from {{G58}}; properly, to go to market, i.e. (by implication) to purchase; specially, to redeem

60.definition: [ἀγοραῖος] from {{G58}}; relating to the market-place, i.e. forensic (times); by implication, vulgar

61.definition: [ἄγρα] from {{G71}}; (abstractly) a catching (of fish); also (concretely) a haul (of fish)

62.definition: [ἀγράμματος] from {{G1}} (as negative particle) and {{G1121}}; unlettered, i.e. illiterate

63.definition: [ἀγραυλέω] from {{G68}} and {{G832}} (in the sense of {{G833}}); to camp out

64.definition: [ἀγρεύω] from {{G61}}; to hunt, i.e. (figuratively) to entrap

66.definition: [ἄγριος] from {{G68}}; wild (as pertaining to the country), literally (natural) or figuratively (fierce)

67.definition: [Ἀγρίππας] apparently from {{G66}} and {{G2462}}; wild-horse tamer; Agrippas, one of the Herods

68.definition: [ἀγρός] from {{G71}}; a field (as a drive for cattle); genitive case, the country; specially, a farm, i.e. hamlet

69.definition: [ἀγρυπνέω] ultimately from {{G1}} (as negative particle) and {{G5258}}; to be sleepless, i.e. keep awake

70.definition: [ἀγρυπνία] from {{G69}}; sleeplessness, i.e. a keeping awake

71.definition: [ἄγω] a primary verb; properly, to lead; by implication, to bring, drive, (reflexively) go, (specially) pass (time), or (figuratively) induce

72.definition: [ἀγωγή] reduplicated from {{G71}}; a bringing up, i.e. mode of living

73.definition: [ἀγών] from {{G71}}; properly, a place of assembly (as if led), i.e. (by implication) a contest (held there); figuratively, an effort or anxiety

74.definition: [ἀγωνία] from {{G73}}; a struggle (properly, the state), i.e. (figuratively) anguish

75.definition: [ἀγωνίζομαι] from {{G73}}; to struggle, literally (to compete for a prize), figuratively (to contend with an adversary), or genitive case (to endeavor to accomplish something)

76.definition: [Ἀδάμ] of Hebrew origin ({{H121}}); Adam, the first man; typically (of Jesus) man (as his representative)

77.definition: [ἀδάπανος] from {{G1}} (as negative particle); and {{G1160}}; costless, i.e. gratuitous

78.definition: [Ἀδδί] probably of Hebrew origin (compare {{H5716}}); Addi, an Israelite

79.definition: [ἀδελφή] feminine of {{G80}}; a sister (naturally or ecclesiastically)

80.definition: [ἀδελφός] from {{G1}} (as a connective particle) and δελφύς (the womb); a brother (literally or figuratively) near or remote (much like {{G1}})

81.definition: [ἀδελφότης] from {{G80}}; brotherhood (properly, the feeling of brotherliness), i.e. the (Christian) fraternity

82.definition: [ἄδηλος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G1212}}; hidden, figuratively, indistinct

85.definition: [ἀδημονέω] from a derivative of ἀδέω (to be sated to loathing); to be in distress (of mind)

86.definition: [ᾅδης] from {{G1}} (as negative particle) and {{G1492}}; properly, unseen, i.e. "Hades" or the place (state) of departed souls

87.definition: [ἀδιάκριτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G1252}}; properly, undistinguished, i.e. (actively) impartial

88.definition: [ἀδιάλειπτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of a compound of {{G1223}} and {{G3007}}; unintermitted, i.e. permanent

89.definition: [ἀδιαλείπτως] adverb from {{G88}}; uninterruptedly, i.e. without omission (on an appropriate occasion)

90.definition: [ἀδιαφθορία] from a derivative of a compound of {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G1311}}; incorruptibleness, i.e. (figuratively) purity (of doctrine)

91.definition: [ἀδικέω] from {{G94}}; to be unjust, i.e. (actively) do wrong (morally, socially or physically)

93.definition: [ἀδικία] from {{G94}}; (legal) injustice (properly, the quality, by implication, the act); morally, wrongfulness (of character, life or act)

94.definition: [ἄδικος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G1349}}; unjust; by extension wicked; by implication, treacherous; specially, heathen

96.definition: [ἀδόκιμος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G1384}}; unapproved, i.e. rejected; by implication, worthless (literally or morally)

97.definition: [ἄδολος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle); and {{G1388}}; undeceitful, i.e. (figuratively) unadulterated

98.definition: [Ἀδραμυττηνός] from Ἀδραμύττειον (a place in Asia Minor); Adramyttene or belonging to Adramyttium

99.definition: [Ἀδρίας] from Ἀδρία (a place near its shore); the Adriatic sea (including the Ionian)
